step by step...




1.  run  NAVSETUP.EXE  and use the keygen to generate your CD Install Key.

2.  once  installed  MAKE SURE YOU ARE NOT CONNECTED TO THE INTERNET! That means: UNPLUG,     DISCONNECT or use a FIREWALL!!

3.  Go  to Product Activation, select "Activate your product now, but skip registration". It will     complain that it cant connect to symantec servers.

4.  Press next untill you get to the retry screen.

5.  Select  "Activate  my  software by phone" and use the keygen once more  to  get your final     unlock code... Mission accomplished, Rest in peace, you can now connect to the internet again.

good luck :)

Hi Guys,

This works a charm if your follow the Steps of DuckOfSteel.

I upgraded to this version after receiving an error of 3019,1 from Norton 2003. It turned out this error is because the virus definition file is now so big (as of May 2010), the memory constraints of 160MB in Norton 2003 can not handle it. 

Without Norton appearing to be keen to fix the problem soon, it was time to upgrade to Norton 2005. As this was the first version with decent memory management.

So without taking on all the challenges of the latest 2010 Norton. I recommend this one, then receive your upgrades through live update.

Now once again I can scan for viruses without that annoying 3019,1 error and so can you :)
